{"questionId": "94ff3e2d", "correctAnswer": ".5", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute the value x = 2", "content": "Replace $x$ with $2$ in $$h(x) = \\frac{8}{5x + 6}.$$ This gives $$h(2) = \\frac{8}{5(2) + 6}.$$"}, {"title": "Compute the result", "content": "Simplify: $$h(2) = \\frac{8}{16} = 0.5.$$ The answer is <strong>.5</strong>."}]}